column2: Sunny- wind 10-15 mph.  4" chop.  No boat traffic.  1 loon in cove.
Sunny- wind 10-15 mph. 3" chop.  No boat traffic.
sunny- light wind- had 13 days prior with some rain
sunny- light wind- had two hot weeks- over four inches of rain in week
sunny- light wind- had 1.5 inches of rain two days ago
Slight chop.  Can see some algae forming.
Pair of loons with 2 young watching us.
Light wind- partly cloudy. Loons with a pair of young.
Lake does not appear to have turned over yet.
Light wind. Young loons on their own now.
4 inch chop. Lake getting lower - no rain.
Partly cloudy. Good chop. Still no rain.
Clear. Slight chop. Had 1.5 inches of rain yesterday.
Partly cloudy- light wind. 1.6 inches of rain yesterday.
can't see any new weed growth
still not much weed growth- lake down about 5 inches
no measurable rain since mid june
had thunder show at noon today
Hoyt Ritter has returned - he's 91 this year
partly cloudy- calm- rain this pm
clear- light chop- last 3 days very windy
partly cloudy- 3" chop. Due to having to take boat out of water after this reading- I was unable to collect any lake turn-over readings.
Partly cloudy- had rain every day this week
Clear; had some rain every day this week
partly cloudy sky; had 2+ inches of rain over weekend
Partly cloudy sky; lake ready to for annual fall turnover
8" chop- third day of high wind
Sunny- hot and humid- wind calm
Last reading--have to take boat out
partly cloudy and humid- good chop
Partly cloudy- good chop- had 3" rain in week
